# Plan: Add `image-text-to-text` Pipeline to Transformers.js

## Context

Transformers.js supports many pipeline tasks but is missing a dedicated `image-text-to-text` pipeline for modern vision-language models (VLMs) like LLaVA, Qwen2-VL, Florence-2, SmolVLM, etc. These models accept an image plus a text prompt and generate text — a distinct pattern from the existing `image-to-text` pipeline, which only does image captioning with no user prompt input. The `AutoModelForImageTextToText` auto-class and all underlying model implementations already exist in `src/models.js`; only the pipeline layer is missing.

**Constraint:** Do NOT modify any existing pipeline classes or their behavior.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `src/pipelines.js` | Primary file — all changes go here |
| `src/models.js` | Read-only reference — `AutoModelForImageTextToText` at line 8736 already exists |
| `src/transformers.js` | No change needed — already does `export * from './pipelines.js'` at line 16 |

---

## Step-by-Step Implementation

### Step 1 — Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to imports

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js`, lines 16–45 (the `import { ... } from './models.js'` block)

Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the existing named-import list (alphabetically after `AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction`, before `AutoModelForImageToImage`):

```js
import {
    // ... existing imports ...
    AutoModelForImageFeatureExtraction,
    AutoModelForImageTextToText,   // ← ADD THIS
    AutoModelForImageToImage,
    // ...
} from './models.js';
```

---

### Step 2 — Add JSDoc typedef block

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js`, after line 2005 (after the closing `}` of `ImageToTextPipeline`)

Follow the exact pattern used by `ImageToTextPipeline` (lines 1943–1954):

```js
/**
 * @typedef {Object} ImageTextToTextSingle
 * @property {string} generated_text The generated text.
 * @typedef {ImageTextToTextSingle[]} ImageTextToTextOutput
 *
 * @callback ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback Process an image and text prompt and generate text.
 * @param {ImagePipelineInputs} images The image(s) to process.
 * @param {string|string[]|Chat|Chat[]} texts The text prompt(s) or chat conversation(s) to condition generation on.
 * @param {Partial<import('./generation/configuration_utils.js').GenerationConfig>} [options] Additional keyword arguments to pass along to the generate method of the model.
 * @returns {Promise<ImageTextToTextOutput|ImageTextToTextOutput[]>} An object (or array of objects) containing the generated text(s).
 *
 * @typedef {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable} ImageTextToTextPipelineType
 */
```

Note: No `PipelineOptions` typedef is needed here (no pipeline-specific options beyond `generate_kwargs`), consistent with `ImageToTextPipeline`.

---

### Step 3 — Add the `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js`, immediately after the typedef block from Step 2 (after line 2005)

Follow the exact class extension cast pattern used by all other pipelines. The `_call` method accepts `(images, texts, generate_kwargs)`, mirrors the chat-template handling from `TextGenerationPipeline` (lines 1013–1028), and uses the processor's combined text+image interface (as VLM processors support `processor(text, image)` returning `{input_ids, attention_mask, pixel_values, ...}`):

```js
/**
 * Image text to text pipeline using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`. This pipeline accepts
 * an image and a text prompt (or chat conversation), and generates text.
 *
 * **Example:** Run a vision-language model with `HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct`.
 * ```javascript
 * const generator = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
 * const image = 'https://huggingface.co/datasets/Xenova/transformers.js-docs/resolve/main/cats.jpg';
 * const messages = [{ role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'image' }, { type: 'text', text: 'Describe this image.' }] }];
 * const output = await generator(image, messages);
 * // [{ generated_text: 'The image shows two cats resting on a couch.' }]
 * ```
 */
export class ImageTextToTextPipeline extends (/** @type {new (options: TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs) => ImageTextToTextPipelineType} */ (Pipeline)) {

    /**
     * Create a new ImageTextToTextPipeline.
     * @param {TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs} options An object used to instantiate the pipeline.
     */
    constructor(options) {
        super(options);
    }

    /** @type {ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback} */
    async _call(images, texts, generate_kwargs = {}) {
        const isBatched = Array.isArray(images) || Array.isArray(texts);
        const preparedImages = await prepareImages(images);

        // Handle chat template inputs (reuse isChat helper defined at line 910)
        const isChatInput = isChat(texts) || (Array.isArray(texts) && texts.every(isChat));
        if (isChatInput) {
            const chatTexts = Array.isArray(texts) && texts.every(isChat) ? texts : [texts];
            texts = chatTexts.map(x => this.processor.apply_chat_template(x, {
                tokenize: false,
                add_generation_prompt: true,
            }));
        } else if (!Array.isArray(texts)) {
            texts = [texts];
        }

        // Processor handles combined text tokenisation + image preprocessing
        const inputs = await this.processor(texts, preparedImages);

        const outputIds = /** @type {Tensor} */ (await this.model.generate({
            ...inputs,
            ...generate_kwargs,
        }));

        // Trim the input prompt tokens, decode only newly generated tokens
        const inputLength = inputs.input_ids.dims.at(-1);
        const decoded = this.tokenizer.batch_decode(
            outputIds.slice(null, [inputLength, null]),
            { skip_special_tokens: true },
        );

        const toReturn = decoded.map(text => [{ generated_text: text.trim() }]);
        return isBatched ? toReturn : toReturn[0];
    }
}
```

**Reused utilities:**
- `prepareImages()` — defined at line 91 in `src/pipelines.js`
- `isChat()` — defined at line 910 in `src/pipelines.js`
- `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` typedef — defined at line 215

---

### Step 4 — Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js`, after the `"image-to-text"` entry (lines 3244–3255), before `"image-classification"`

```js
"image-text-to-text": {
    "tokenizer": AutoTokenizer,
    "pipeline": ImageTextToTextPipeline,
    "model": AutoModelForImageTextToText,
    "processor": AutoProcessor,
    "default": {
        "model": "HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct",
    },
    "type": "multimodal",
},
```

This follows the exact same structure as `"image-to-text"` and `"document-question-answering"`, which are both `"multimodal"` tasks with `tokenizer` + `model` + `processor`.

---

### Step 5 — Update `pipeline()` function JSDoc

**Location:** `src/pipelines.js`, within the `pipeline()` function's `@param {T} task` JSDoc block (around lines 3418–3440)

Add a new bullet after the `"image-to-text"` line:

```
 *  - `"image-text-to-text"`: will return a `ImageTextToTextPipeline`.
```

---

## Summary of All Changes (single file: `src/pipelines.js`)

| # | Location | What |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Import block (lines 16–45) | Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to named imports from `./models.js` |
| 2 | After line 2005 | Add `@typedef` JSDoc block for `ImageTextToTextSingle`, `ImageTextToTextOutput`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineType` |
| 3 | After line 2005 (same location, after typedef) | Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class with `constructor` + `_call` |
| 4 | `SUPPORTED_TASKS` (after line 3255) | Add `"image-text-to-text"` task entry |
| 5 | `pipeline()` JSDoc (around line 3427) | Add `"image-text-to-text"` to task list description |

---

## Verification

1. **Import check:** Confirm no `AutoModelForImageTextToText` import error by searching `src/models.js` exports — it is exported at line 8736.
2. **Functional test:** Instantiate the pipeline with a small VLM:
   ```js
   import { pipeline } from '@huggingface/transformers';
   const generator = await pipeline('image-text-to-text', 'HuggingFaceTB/SmolVLM-256M-Instruct');
   const output = await generator(imageUrl, [{ role: 'user', content: [{ type: 'image' }, { type: 'text', text: 'What is in this image?' }] }]);
   console.log(output); // [{ generated_text: '...' }]
   ```
3. **Type safety check:** Verify the `ImageTextToTextPipelineType` typedef properly intersects `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs & ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback & Disposable`.
4. **Batch test:** Pass an array of images and texts and verify the output is an array of arrays.
5. **String text test:** Pass a plain string (non-Chat) as `texts` and verify it works via the `!Array.isArray(texts)` branch.
6. **Existing tests:** Run the existing test suite to confirm no regressions — no existing pipeline classes are modified.

